# Other applications
OOD Detection (Out-of-Distribution): 當 Target 和 Proxy 的特徵對齊 $Z_P W \approx Z_T$ 突然崩潰時，代表遇到 OOD 資料。
Generalization Forecasting: 也就是你前面提到的 Control Variate 應用。

# abstract
Abstract 的黃金結構 (150-200 字)：
背景與痛點： 現代模型 (如 LLMs) 評估與 Hyperparameter 搜尋成本極高，亟需輕量級的 Proxy 模型。
現有解法缺陷： 現有的幾何相似度 (如 CKA) 缺乏與真實風險 (Functional Risk) 的嚴格理論連結。
我們的方法 (PRISM)： 提出基於 Nuclear Norm 的 Procrustes Similarity，推導出精確的風險誤差上界 (Risk Bound)，將誤差拆解為 Scale, Shape, 與 Head 影響。
實驗與應用： 在量化 (AWQ/GPTQ) 與微調 (LoRA/SFT) 上，證明理論指標與真實效能下降具有極高相關性 ($\rho > 0.9$)，並能用 500 筆樣本精準預測整體效能，大幅節省計算資源。

# Limitations and Future Work
While PRISM establishes a rigorous foundation for geometric risk estimation, several promising avenues remain for future exploration:
 - Label-Free Performance Monitoring in Production: Since our geometric bounds ($\Omega$, $\Delta \rho$) rely exclusively on feature matrices and do not require ground-truth labels $y$, future work could deploy PRISM as an online, label-free safety monitor to detect semantic degradation or OOD shifts in deployed LLMs.
 - Dynamic Trajectory Alignment for Long CoT: Our current formulation validates static prefill manifolds. Extending the isometric alignment to dynamic, multi-step generation trajectories would enable proxy estimation for complex reasoning tasks, such as long Chain-of-Thought (CoT) and agentic loops.
 - Cross-Modal and Non-LLM Generalization: Though empirically validated on LLMs, the Linear Representation Hypothesis extends beyond text. Future research should investigate the applicability of our Procrustes-based framework to cross-modal models (e.g., CLIP) and vision transformers, analyzing whether modalities share isomorphic semantic topologies.
 - non-transformer-based model
